# SDUI JSON Configuration

This project uses JSON-driven UI with composition. **Never hardcode layout or shared UI in React**—define everything in JSON.

## Layouts
- Use `layout: "store"` or `layout: "account"` in screen config to wrap content with shared navbar + footer
- Layouts live in `config/layouts/` and define structure with `$slot`
- Navbar and footer are inlined in each layout with `"_shared": { "id": "sc-navbar", "name": "Navbar" }` metadata

## Shared Components
- All reusable UI is defined in `config/shared-components.json` as named models
- Each model has `id`, `name`, `properties: []`, and a full `content` tree
- When placing a shared component in a layout or screen, inline the full `content` tree with `"_shared": { "id": "sc-id", "name": "Name" }` on the root node
- The `_shared` marker lets the builder track which model an instance came from

