## Key Order (UI nodes)
Use this order for predictable AI scanning: 1. `type` 2. `props` 3. `condition` 4. `map`/`key` 5. `children` 6. `actions` 7. `text`/`$slot`

## Navigation (no hardcoded paths)
- Static: `{ "action": "navigate", "payload": { "path": "/shop" } }`
- Dynamic (e.g. product detail): `{ "action": "navigate", "payload": { "routeConfig": "product", "slug": { "var": "$item.slug" } } }`—route path comes from `config/routes.json`.

## Theme & Colors
- Use theme variables: `text-[var(--theme-foreground)]`, `bg-[var(--theme-announcement-bg)]`—never hardcoded hex colors.
- Theme defined in `config/theme.json` (colors, sections.announcement, sections.header, sections.hero).

## Content Slot
- Layouts use `"$slot": "content"` as placeholder; screen `content` is injected there
- `content` can be a single node or array (e.g. main content + modals)

## Screen Structure
```json
{
  "meta": { "title": "..." },
  "state": {},
  "layout": "store",
  "content": { ... }
}
```
Screens without `layout` use `ui` directly (e.g. login, signup).
